          "source_html": "<div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 27 - 31</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>YES</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose</span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong> NO </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">27</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The delay in the process used by the Kellogg brothers affected the final product.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. YES</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问Kellogg兄弟延误的加工过程是否影响了最终产品。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词: Kellogg brothers，delay，affected the final product</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: A段，One day, the brothers left cooked wheat untended for more than 24 hours. When they returned, they saw what they had done. It was no good to eat, but they decided to run the stale wheat through rollers, just to see how it would turn out. Normally, the process produced long sheets, but they were surprised to discover that this time the rollers created flat flakes. They baked them, and then tried the same thing with corn.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;A段指出，他们不小心让小麦放置了超过24小时，最后做出了小薄片（flakes）而不是往常的大薄片（long sheets）。</p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">28</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Sir Alan Hodgkin is an example of someone whose work proceeded in a logical and systematic way.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问Alan Hodgkin的工作是否按照逻辑和系统进行。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词: Alan Hodgkin，logical and systematic</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: B段，Nobel laureate Sir Alan Hodgkin, who discovered how nerve cells transmit electrical impulses between the skin and the brain, commented: &#39;I believe that the record of my published papers conveys an impression of directedness and planning which does not at all coincide with the actual sequence of events.’</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;B段指出Hodgkin的研究成果在发表后的确表现出一种有计划和有方向的印象，但实际研究过程并不是有条不紊或按部就班的。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：logical and systematic way = impression of directedness and planning</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">29</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Daguerre is an exception to the general rule of innovation.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问Daguerre是否是创新规则的例外。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词: Daguerre，exception</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: C段，The same rule applies in business. The mistake that gave us cornflakes keeps repeating itself in the history of disruptive innovation, the kind that transforms markets. Louis Daguerre, for instance, discovered the technique that gave us photography in the 1830s, when drops of mercury from a shattered thermometer produced a photographic image.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;C段指出Daguerre的发现也是通过意外发生的，因此他并不是例外。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">30</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The discovery of saccharin occurred by accident during drug research.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. YES</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问糖精是否是在药物研究中的意外发现。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词: saccharin，discovered by accident，drug research</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: &nbsp;C段，The artificial sweetener, saccharin, was the unintentional result of a medical scientist’s work on a chemical treatment for gastric ulcers.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:C段指出糖精是研究胃溃疡药物时的意外发现。</p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p>同义替换：accident =&nbsp; unintentional result; drug research = medical scientist’s work</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">31</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The company 3M should have supported Art Fry by funding his idea of Post-It Notes.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. NOT GIVEN</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键信息：<br/></p><p>3M, Art Fry, Post-It Notes</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：</p><p>C段，While working for the firm 3M, researcher Art Fry had no idea he was taking the first steps towards Post-It Notes when he used bits of adhesive office paper that could be easily lifted off the page to replace the scrap paper bookmarks that kept falling out of his hymn book.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：C段没有指出 3M 公司是否应该为 Art Fry 的便利贴（Post-It Notes）创意提供资金支持。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><strong>Questions 32 - 35</strong></p><p><br/></p><p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending. Choose the correct ending and move it into the gap.</p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"word-bank-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"wb-title\">Options (Word Bank):</div>\r\n        <div class=\"wb-grid\">\r\n            <div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>A.</strong> can be found in unusual thoughts and chance events.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>B.</strong> can be taught in business schools.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>C.</strong> has made a success from someone else’s invention.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>D.</strong> is designed to nurture differences.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>E.</strong> is unlikely to lead to creative innovation.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>F.</strong> says that all mistakes are the same.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>G.</strong> shows that businesses are good at either inventing or selling.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>H.</strong> suggests ways of increasing the number of mistakes.</div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"matrix-container\">\r\n        <table>\r\n            <thead><tr><th class=\"corner-header\">Question / Paragraph</th><th>A</th><th>B</th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th><th>G</th><th>H</th></tr></thead>\r\n            <tbody>\r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">32</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p>The usual business environment <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_32\" value=\"H\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"9\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：E</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词: usual business environment</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: D段，Breakthrough and disruptive innovation are rarely driven by orderly process. Usually they come out of a chaotic, haphazard mess, which is why big companies, full of managers schooled in business programmes designed to eliminate random variation and mistakes, struggle with them. In these sorts of environments, accidents are called failures and are discouraged.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:D段指出常规的商业环境往往由排除随机变化和错误的管理体系主导，这些体系不鼓励“意外”发生，因此不利于创新。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">33</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p>Geroski and Markides&#39;s book <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_33\" value=\"H\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"9\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：G</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词: Geroski and Markides</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: E段，Their book, Fast Second, divides businesses into &#39;colonists’ and &#39;consolidators’. Small and nimble, colonists are adept at creating market niches but are terrible institution builders.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;E段指出Geroski和Markides的书讨论了企业要么擅长创新，要么擅长商业化，而很少两者兼备。</p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">34</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p>Microsoft is an example of a company which <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_34\" value=\"H\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"9\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：C</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词: Microsoft</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: E段，Consolidators, with their strong cultures of discipline and cost control, know how to take clever ideas from other firms and turn them into mass-market items. Microsoft is a prime instance of this.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;E段指出微软是“consolidator”（整合者）的一个例子，他们擅长将其他公司发明的点子转化为大众市场产品。</p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">35</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p>The origin of useful accidents <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55621_35\" value=\"H\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"9\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：A</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词: origin of useful accidents</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: F段，Accidents, they say, come from unlikely mental associations such as memories and vague connections, looking for something and finding it in an unexpected way, looking for one thing and finding something else, and not looking for anything but finding something valuable.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:F段指出有用的意外往往源自于偶然的联想和事件。原文指出这些意外是来自于“unusual thoughts”（不同寻常的想法）和“unexpected way”（意想不到的方式）。</p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 36 - 40</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose the correct answer.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">36</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>How do Austin and Devin advise companies to get out of the &#39;cone of expectation&#39;?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> by decreasing the number of company systems</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> by forming teams of different types of people</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> by hiring new and creative people</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> by holding regular brainstorming meetings</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. by forming teams of different types of people</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键词: &nbsp;Austin and Devin，get out of the cone of expectation</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: G段，It means throwing together groups from diverse backgrounds, and combining ideas in unpredictable ways. Other strategies also include having systems that watch out for accidents and examine them for value, generating them when they do not happen often enough, seizing on the useful ones, capturing their valuable features, and building on them to add value and give potential for useful accidents.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:G段指出Austin和Devin建议公司通过让来自不同背景的人组成团队来突破预期。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：brainstorming meetings = combining ideas</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">37</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>In recommending &#39;counter-intuitive&#39; thinking, what do Austin and Devin imply?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> that failing at business is bad for staff morale</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> that innovation cannot be planned for</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> that most businesses should be devoted to avoiding mistakes</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> that the cost of mistakes is an important consideration</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. that innovation cannot be planned for</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键词: Austin and Devin，counter-intuitive thinking</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: H段，It runs counter to the notion frequently pushed by consultants that you can &#39;harness&#39; creativity and direct it to line up with intention. &#39;The cost of accidents that do not prove valuable is often a concern to people in business,&#39; they write. &#39;In business, people tend to call such efforts failure.&#39;</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;H段指出与大多数商业管理人员的观念不同，Austin和Devin认为创新不能通过计划实现。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">38</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The writer describes the Empire Lager disaster in order to show that</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> success can come out of a business failure.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> the majority of companies now value risk-taking.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> TV advertising works better on older people.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> young beer drinkers do not like a sweet taste.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. success can come out of a business failure.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键词: Empire Lager disaster</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: J段，Instead of wiping the unsuccessful product launch, Foster’s used this lesson learned to go on and develop other brands instead.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:&nbsp;J段指出Fosters从Empire Lager的失败吸取教训，创造其他成功的品牌。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">39</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Pure Blonde has been more successful than Empire Lager because</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> digital media other than TV were used.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> it was advertised under a different brand name.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> it was launched with very little advertising.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> the advertising budget was larger.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. it was launched with very little advertising.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键词: Pure Blonde，Empire Lager，more successful</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: J段，One of them, Pure Blonde, is now ranked as Australia’s fifth-largest beer brand. Unlike Empire Lager, there has been almost no promotion and its sales are generated more by word of mouth.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:J段指出与Empire Lager不同，Pure Blonde几乎没有广告宣传，因此成功更多依赖口碑传播。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：very little advertising =almost no promotion</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">40</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The writer concludes that creating a culture that learns from mistakes</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> brings short-term financial gains.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> can be very difficult for some companies.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> holds no risk for workers.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> is a popular move with shareholders.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. can be very difficult for some companies.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>定位关键词: creating a culture，learns from mistakes</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: K段，In a market that focuses on the short-term, convincing employees and shareholders to tolerate failure and not play it safe is a big thing to ask.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路:K段指出, 想要创建一种从错误中学习的文化对许多公司来说是困难的。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>",
